<p><a name="Interrogative_pronouns" id="Interrogative_pronouns"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Latin_declension&amp;action=edit&amp;section=19" title="Edit section: Interrogative pronouns">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Interrogative pronouns</span></h3>
<p>The interrogative pronouns are used strictly for asking questions. It is best not to confuse them with the relative pronoun and the interrogative adjective (which is declined like the relative pronoun). Interrogative pronouns rarely occur in the plural, though they may. The plural interrogative pronouns are the same as the plural relative pronouns.</p>
<table class="wikitable">
<tr>
<th rowspan="2"></th>
<th colspan="1"><b><i>quis</i><br />
who? m. and f.</b></th>
<th colspan="1"><b><i>quid</i><br />
what? n. only</b></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<th colspan="2"><b>Singular</b></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<th><b>Nominative</b></th>
<td>quis</td>
<td>quid</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th><b>Genitive</b></th>
<td>cuius</td>
<td>cuius</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th><b>Dative</b></th>
<td>cui</td>
<td>cui</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th><b>Accusative</b></th>
<td>quem</td>
<td>quid</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th><b>Vocative</b></th>
<td>-</td>
<td>-</td>
